news.title: Karnataka: Panel suggests conversion of B Khata to A Khata by levying compounding fee
news.para: The committee has said: “Suitable rules can be framed under Section 76F of the Karnataka Town and Country Planning (KTCP) act for compounding offence, B Khata sites can be converted to A Khata by paying land conversion fees and fines and compounding fees to the concerned planning authority.”

news.title: Refund details being worked out for Chintels Paradiso residents: Gurugram DC
news.para: Gurugram District Commissioner Nishant Yadav said the details for the refund will be worked out soon. Yadav visited the society on Friday to oversee ongoing repairs and rehabilitation of the residents of the partially collapsed tower.

news.title: With complaints galore, Karnataka RERA intensifies spot inspections
news.para: The Karnataka Real Estate Regulatory Authority (K-RERA) has intensified spot inspections to verify claims of developers on the status of projects. This comes in the wake of complaints pouring in from homebuyers now that the pandemic pangs have eased.

news.title: MahaRERA website set to display complaints on projects, promoters
news.para: Maharashtra Real Estate Regulatory Authority (MahaRERA) authorities said the arrangement would help the homebuyers take an informed decision before investing in any project.

news.title: RP gets 16 insolvency resolution plans from nine bidders for HDIL
news.para: "The Resolution Professional is in the process of examining the resolution plans in accordance with the provisions of the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016, and Regulations framed thereunder," the filing said.

news.title: SWAMIH Investment Fund gives final approval to 105 proposals
news.para: In November 2019, the centre had announced a Rs 25,000-crore fund -- Special Window for Affordable & Mid-Income Housing (SWAMIH)-- to help complete over 1,500 stalled housing projects comprising 4.58 lakh housing units across the country.

news.title: Shimao Group slips on loan payment delay plans, asset freeze reports
news.para: Shimao proposed to creditors on Wednesday it would repay the onshore trust loan in states in the next three years, of which 1.3 billion yuan ($205.36 million) would become due on Thursday, sources told Reuters.

news.title: Tamil Nadu DVAC obtains approval to prosecute official in illegal sand mining case
news.para: ​Recording this, Justice G Chandrasekaran closed a criminal original petition from Gnanarajan of Upparpatti village in Theni district, who prayed for a direction to the DVAC to register a case on his complaint dated July 15, 2021 and proceed further against the accused.

news.title: Dehradun: Hillocks along Rispana river being flattened, say concerned residents
news.para: The latest incidence of brazen flattening of a hillock has taken place near Tarla Nagal on Rajpur road where a private builder is starting a project on nearly 2 acres land. Residents of the area are claiming that the Jaipur-based firm has flattened nearly 7-8 acres land.

news.title: Chinese cities ease home purchase down-payments to reignite demand
news.para: The eastern city of Heze is allowing some home buyers to pay lower down-payments for their purchases, two sources with direct knowledge of the matter said late on Thursday, among the first cities easing the borrowing rule.

news.title: Pune: GB nod to no property tax increase proposal
news.para: Last week, the standing committee had approved not to hike the property and entertainment tax for the next financial year.

news.title: ED files fresh chargesheet against Unitech group, promoters in money laundering case
news.para: ​The chargesheet was filed on Thursday before the Rouse Avenue court here and the court has taken cognisance of the prosecution compliant field under various sections of the Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA), it said.

news.title: Correct discrepancies in records: HC panel tells Nagpur civic body, NIT
news.para: While flaying both authorities for the mismatch in the measurements of same plots, Justice (retired) Zaka Haq, heading the commission, granted one more chance to the NMC Town Planning Department’s assistant director and NIT executive officer for re-examining and correcting discrepancies in their records and submit a fresh affidavit.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body offers 25% tax discount on houses of 40-70 sq metres
news.para: A release from Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation (AMC) said that it has announced this flat discount for 2022-23. The decision was taken in the meeting of the civic body’s standing committee held on Thursday.

news.title: Zomato leases three lakh sq ft office space in Gurugram
news.para: "The building where Zomato has taken space is a JV (joint venture) between Emaar India and another developer. Zomato has relocated from existing space and an international property consultant facilitated the deal," a person aware of the deal said on condition of anonymity.
